@startuml
title Detection and Face Lock for Export Ready Redaction
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  ArrowFontColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #05D887
  ParticipantFontColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontStyle bold
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #05D887
  ActorFontColor #111111
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F4FFF9
  BorderColor #05D887
  FontColor #111111
}
actor User
participant "Frontend\nVideo Editor" as FE
participant "Flask API\nPipeline" as API
database "Local Storage\noutput and snaps" as Store
participant "TwelveLabs\nIndexed Video" as TLIndex
participant "TwelveLabs\nAnalysis and Entity Search" as TLAnalysis
participant "OpenCV\nVideo and Tracking" as OpenCV
participant "OpenCV ResNet10\nFace Detector" as ResNet
participant "InsightFace\nIdentity Matching" as InsightFace
participant "Ultralytics YOLO\nObject Detection" as YOLO
participant "FFmpeg\nMP4 Encoding" as FFmpeg
User -> FE: Open indexed video in editor
FE -> API: GET /api/jobs/by-video/{video_id}?ensure=true
API -> Store: Look for existing local processing job
Store --> API: existing job or no match
API -> OpenCV: Read video metadata
OpenCV --> API: duration, fps, width, height
API -> TLAnalysis: Describe people, objects, and scenes\nwhen video id is available
note right of TLAnalysis
Model
TwelveLabs analyze provides people, object,
and scene context. The pipeline uses these
timestamps to choose better keyframes when available.
end note
TLAnalysis --> API: people, object, and scene context
API -> OpenCV: Extract keyframes from analysis timestamps\nor fallback time interval
OpenCV --> API: keyframes
API -> ResNet: Detect generic face boxes on keyframes
API -> InsightFace: Create face embeddings and identity evidence
API -> YOLO: Detect supported object classes
note right of YOLO
Model
ResNet10 finds face boxes.
InsightFace supports identity matching.
YOLO finds object boxes for object redaction.
end note
ResNet --> API: face boxes
InsightFace --> API: face embeddings and appearances
YOLO --> API: object boxes
API -> API: Cluster detections into unique people and objects
API -> Store: Save detection metadata and face/object snapshots
Store --> API: local job ready
API --> FE: job id, ready status, video metadata
FE -> API: GET /api/faces/{job_id}\nGET /api/objects/{job_id}
API -> Store: Load saved detections and snapshots
Store --> API: unique faces, objects, timestamps
API --> FE: faces, objects, scene summary
FE --> User: Show detections and timeline context
User -> FE: Select person for export-ready redaction
FE -> API: GET /api/face-lock-track/{job_id}/{person_id}?include_lane=true
API -> Store: Check saved face-lock lane
Store --> API: lane missing or stale
API --> FE: status missing
FE -> API: POST /api/face-lock-track/build\njob_id, person_id
API -> Store: Load source video and selected person's saved appearances
API -> TLAnalysis: Optional entity time-range search\nfor this selected person
TLAnalysis --> API: target appearance ranges
API -> OpenCV: Build frame-by-frame face-lock lane\nusing trackers and motion cues
API -> InsightFace: Verify or relock selected identity\ninside search region
note right of InsightFace
Face-lock starts only after detection metadata exists.
It uses the selected person's saved appearances as anchors,
then OpenCV tracking fills the frames between anchors.
[OpenCV CSRT tracking + Lucas-Kanade optical flow + 
global motion compensation + bbox smoothing + velocity prediction 
and search-region expansion across gaps ]
end note
OpenCV --> API: tracked boxes by frame
InsightFace --> API: identity-confirmed relock boxes
API -> Store: Save face-lock lane
Store --> API: lane ready
FE -> API: Poll /api/face-lock-track/{job_id}/{person_id}
API --> FE: ready lane
FE --> User: Show locked status and preview overlay

@enduml